            <img class="img-responsive" style='height: 650px; width:470px; left:30.5%;' src="img/anatomy.png" alt="">
            <!--In the original application, these points are injected with Javascript, but ideally, they'd be injected with a haml loop. Because I'm hardcoding content, I'm presenting this as prerendered HTML-->
            <button class="map-point" style="top:40%;left:45%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Mantle</h2>
                  <p>is the loose outer tissue that covers the entire body of the oyster. The mantle is always in contact with the shell but is not attached to it. The primary function of the mantle is to produce the oyster shell.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:38%;left:57%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Labial Palps</h2>
                  <p>are specialized organs that control the total amount of food that is passed along to the mouth.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:38%;left:51%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Viceral Mass</h2>
                  <p>contains organs for digestion, reproduction, excretion and circulation.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:61%;left:55.5%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Connective Tissue</h2>
                  <p>serves as transport system for oxygen and other nutrients.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:49%;left:52%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Lower Intestine</h2>
                  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Etiam ac imperdiet nulla. Nulla blandit nisi lorem, nec mollis magna aliquam finibus. Integer malesuada, lorem a tristique porta, metus felis aliquet eros, quis.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:63%;left:50%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Adductor Muscle</h2>
                  <p>is the organ where most of the digestion and food absorption takes place.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:47%;left:57%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Gills</h2>
                  <p>are the main respiratory organ but also play a role in feeding. By beating tiny hairs called cilia, the gills are able to create a current pumping water over the gills. By this method the gills are able to collect food particles.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:55.5%;left:50%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Pericardial Cavity</h2>
                  <p>contains the heart and contains fluid that serves as a lubricant to allow easy heart movement.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
            <button class="map-point" style="top:56%;left:45.5%">
              <div class="content">
                <div class="centered-y">
                  <h2>Rectum</h2>
                  <p>can be found along the edge of the adductor muscle. It is a tube through which wastes are eliminated.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </button>
